Package: countallmissing
Title: Count All Missing Values 
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Hannah", "Hauch", , "hhauch00@student.ubc.ca", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "YOUR-ORCID-ID"))
Description: The goal of countallmissing is to count missing values for all columns by group in a data set. 
  This function is a wrapper around the `group_by()` and `summarize()` functions in the `dplyr` package. 
  Given a data frame `data` and a column `group`, **count_all_missing_by_group()** creates a new data frame with one row per level of `group`.
  The first column of the output data frame contains the levels of `group`, and the rest of the columns contain the number of missing values for all columns in `data` except `group`.
